1.
It's a protocol for transmitting web documents. 
It has request methods 
GET (retrieve data), 
POST (submit data), 
PUT (update resources),
DELETE (remove resources), and others as well.

2.
API stands for Application Programming Interface 
It's a set of rules for software interaction. 
JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) is a format for structuring data exchanged between APIs, characterized by its readable format and ease of use

3.
A technique for creating dynamic web pages that update content asynchronously, allowing web applications to function without having to reload the entire page. 
Asynchronous code in programming executes tasks in the background, improving efficiency and user experience by not blocking other operations.
